        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Rumania)/7–2345:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 811<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Representative in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRM1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Melbourne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-23T19:00:00+02:00">July 23, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>495. See Telegram <gloss target="#t_M1">M</gloss>–1285 July 23 [<hi rend="italic">24</hi>]<note n="1" xml:id="d811fn1">
                        <ref target="#d812">Document No. 812</ref>.</note> sent by <persName corresp="#p_SBGCTVR1">Schuyler</persName> to <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> outlining and asking for comment on his
                    proposed course of action in view of Soviet proposed <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss> procedure. General considers and I concur it is necessary to
                    make clear American viewpoint on significant continuing unilateral actions taken
                    by Soviet officials on <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss> or risk assumption
                    that now they are countenanced by <persName corresp="#p_SBGCTVR1">Schuyler</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Melbourne</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
